[3] South America (Venezuela)
Date: Thu 29 Mar 2018
Source: El Sol de San Juan del Rio [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
https://www.elsoldesanjuandelrio.com.mx/local/brote-de-varicela-en-la-valla-1573337.html


Mothers of the primary school "Jose Vasconcelos" of the community of La Valla, called for the support of the health authority to prevent further infections of varicella in the area Rosalia Nieves Rosas

A group of mothers of primary school "Jose Vasconcelos" of the community of La Valla, expressed their concern over the outbreak of Chickenpox and to date, no authority has visited to control and eradicate the virus.

Yesterday [Wed 28 Mar 2018] mothers of the primary school sought to solicit the support of the health authorities to attend a community meeting with the locals to offer information and recommendations to prevent more people from becoming infected by this virus.

As a personal initiative some of the parents chose not to take their children to school to avoid spreading others lower.

They mentioned that for each group at least 2 children were contagious. For this reason, they called for the support of competent authorities in order to prevent further cases of children with this virus, since during this seasonal period it is common to see infection with Varicella.

[Byline: Rosalia Nieves Rosas]

